# Accessibility

Baseline: **WCAG 2.2 Level AA**. Source of truth:
`design-system/accessibility.md`. Read it before adding a new
interaction. The rules below are the binding short version.

## Required on every interactive element

1. **Semantic HTML.** `<button>`, `<a>`, `<input>`, `<select>`,
   `<textarea>`, `<dialog>` — not `<div>` or `<span>` with handlers.
2. **Accessible name.** Visible text, `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby`.
   Icon-only buttons must have one.
3. **Keyboard reachable.** Tab order matches visual order. Enter and
   Space activate buttons identically.
4. **Visible focus ring.** Never `outline-none` / `outline: none` without
   a replacement of equal or better contrast. Use the `ring` utility
   bound to `--color-focus-ring`.
5. **Touch target 44×44 CSS px** on touch viewports. The `Button`
   `size="icon"` variant ships at `h-11 w-11`. Icon-only controls in
   dense rows must have a 44×44 hit area via padding.
6. **Color is never the only signal.** Errors are red **and** labelled
   (or carry an icon). PR state is gold **and** carries "PR". Required
   fields have an asterisk **and** `aria-required`.

## Forms

- **Wrap every input in `FormField`** (`@famm/ui`). Never use a bare
  `<input>` in feature code.
- The label is associated with the control via `htmlFor` / `id`. The
  `FormField` pattern wires this automatically.
- Errors:
  - `aria-invalid="true"` on the control.
  - Error message has `role="alert"` and is linked via
    `aria-describedby`.
  - Error text lives below the field, not in a tooltip.
- Required fields: visible asterisk **and** `aria-required="true"`.
- Set `autocomplete` where applicable (`email`, `tel`, `current-password`,
  `one-time-code`, `cc-number`, …).
- Numbers: `inputMode="numeric"` for reps/weights; `inputMode="decimal"`
  only when fractions are actually allowed.

## Screen readers

- **Live data** that changes (timers, set counters, async results) is
  inside an `aria-live="polite"` region.
- **Critical messages** (failed save, expired session) use
  `role="alert"` — they announce immediately.
- **Modals**: `aria-modal="true"` + `aria-labelledby` on the title.
  Focus is trapped while open; focus returns to the trigger on close.
- **Decorative icons** carry `aria-hidden="true"`.
- **Meaningful icons** carry an `aria-label`.

## Keyboard

- **Escape** closes modals, popovers, menus; focus returns to trigger.
- **Arrow keys** navigate within composite widgets (tabs, listbox,
  calendar). **Tab** moves between widgets.
- **Enter/Space** activate buttons identically.
- **No keyboard traps** outside intentional focus traps (modals).

## Motion & reduced motion

- Animations > 200ms or involving translation must branch on
  `useReducedMotion()` from `@famm/ui`.
- Tokens already collapse `--duration-*` to `0ms` inside
  `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` — so a transition driven purely by
  `duration-fast`/`base`/`slow` is reduced for free.
- No auto-playing video, no parallax, no infinite loops (except active
  loading indicators).

## Contrast — non-negotiable

- Body text ≥ **4.5:1** against its background.
- Large text (≥ 18px or ≥ 14px bold) ≥ **3:1**.
- Meaningful UI graphics (icons, focus rings, form borders) ≥ **3:1**.
- Tokens are pre-validated. **If you introduce a raw color (you
  shouldn't — see `04-design-tokens.mdc`), include the contrast ratio
  in your `Design-system decisions` block.**

## What CI enforces

- `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y/recommended` + tightened overrides
  (`no-autofocus`, `click-events-have-key-events`,
  `no-static-element-interactions`, `anchor-is-valid`).
- `no-restricted-syntax` bans raw hex/px/rgb and inline `style={}`
  outside L1 primitives.

## What CI can't catch (you must)

- Logical tab order.
- `aria-label` text quality (it should describe the *action*, not the
  *icon*).
- Live regions actually announcing what the user needs.
- Focus ring visible against this surface (not just *some* surface).
- Destructive state still reads as destructive in dark mode.

## After editing — explain

Include in your `Design-system decisions:` block:

- `A11y:` keyboard reachable, focus ring on `<Button>` and custom
  control, `aria-live` added to set counter, `useReducedMotion` branch
  on celebrate animation.
- `OPEN:` items the user must verify manually — screen-reader pass on
  the new modal, focus order in landscape phone view.
